    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-05-16T22:30:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-05-16T22:30:00-05:00" n="376"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d376">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">756D.5–MAP/5–1751: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Indonesia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Cochran</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Djakarta</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-05-17T11:00:00+07:30"
                            >May 17, 1951—11 a. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1609. Djuanda came my home 2 p. m. May 16. <gloss target="#t_Deptel1"
                        >Deptel</gloss> 1249 had reached me. I was consequently able confirm and
                    expand certain ideas given Djuanda previous eve on procurement mil equip by
                        <gloss target="#t_Indo1">Indo</gloss> (<gloss target="#t_Embtel1"
                        >Embtel</gloss> 1597).<note n="1" xml:id="d376fn1">Not printed; see footnote
                        5, <hi rend="italic">supra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>Do not contemplate further mention arms procurement to <gloss target="#t_Indo1"
                        >Indo</gloss> in present atmosphere. Djuanda agrees with me that best
                    eventual approach might be thru Hatta to Sukiman.</p>
                <p>Am most appreciative of alacrity and completeness with which Dept <pb facs="0674"
                        n="656" xml:id="pg_656"/> has kept me informed as to policy and supported
                    with background info in present emergency.<note n="2" xml:id="d376fn2">In
                        telegram 1625 from Djakarta, May 21, which is not here printed, Ambassador
                        Cochran had a conversation that day with Mr. Djuanda, and they agreed that
                        the Ambassador should not invite discussion of another <gloss
                            target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss> accord until President Sukarno had
                        returned to Djakarta on May 27 and until after the government had issued a
                        major policy statement to Parliament on May 28. The Ambassador also added
                        privately that after May 28, he was also considering making a secret
                        approach to Dr. Hatta regarding the consummation of another <gloss
                            target="#t_MDAP1">MDAP</gloss> accord. (756D.5–MAP/5–2151)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cochran</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
